contentrichtext.text: The '''[[Wappinger]]''' were an American tribe native to eastern New York. The term "Wappinger" may also refer to: * [[Wappinger, New York]], the Town of Wappinger named for the tribe * [[Wappingers Falls, New York]], a village located in the Town of Wappinger and the Town of Poughkeepsie * [[Wappinger Creek]], a tributary of the Hudson River * [[Wappinger Fault]], a fault line under the town * [[Wappingers Central School District]] * [[Kieft's War]], also known as the ''Wappinger War'', a 17th century conflict between the Dutch and the Native Americans {{disambig}}
